## 1. Razorpay Setup

### How Your Code Uses Razorpay

Your payment flow works like this:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant F as Frontend (React)
    participant B as Backend (Express)
    participant R as Razorpay API
    participant DB as MongoDB

    U->>F: Click "Pay â‚ą499"
    F->>B: POST /api/payment/create-order
    B->>B: Validate input (Zod)
    B->>B: Check duplicates
    B->>DB: Create Registration (status: pending)
    B->>R: razorpay.orders.create()
    R-->>B: Order ID
    B-->>F: { orderId, amount, currency }
    F->>R: Open Razorpay Checkout popup
    U->>R: Enter card / UPI
    R-->>F: Payment success callback
    R->>B: POST /api/payment/webhook (server-to-server)
    B->>B: Verify HMAC signature
    B->>DB: Update status â†’ "paid" (atomic)
    B->>B: Queue: Email + QR + Google Sheets
```

### Step 1: Create Razorpay Account

1. Go to [https://dashboard.razorpay.com/signup](https://dashboard.razorpay.com/signup)
2. Sign up with your email
3. Complete KYC verification (required for live payments)

### Step 2: Get Test Keys (Development)

1. Login to [Razorpay Dashboard](https://dashboard.razorpay.com)
2. Go to **Settings** â†’ **API Keys**
3. Switch to **Test Mode** (toggle at top-left)
4. Click **Generate Test Key**
5. You'll get:
   - `Key ID` â†’ starts with `rzp_test_`
   - `Key Secret` â†’ shown once, **copy immediately**

### Step 3: Get Live Keys (Production)

1. Same dashboard â†’ switch to **Live Mode**
2. **Generate Live Key** (requires KYC approval)
3. You'll get:
   - `Key ID` â†’ starts with `rzp_live_`
   - `Key Secret` â†’ shown once, **copy immediately**

> [!CAUTION]
> **NEVER commit your Key Secret to Git.** It goes ONLY in your server `.env` file and GitHub Secrets. Your code already handles this correctly â€” the secret is only used server-side in [razorpayService.js](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/services/razorpayService.js).

### Step 4: Set Up Webhook

1. In Razorpay Dashboard â†’ **Settings** â†’ **Webhooks**
2. Click **Add New Webhook**
3. Configure:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Webhook URL** | `https://yourdomain.com/api/payment/webhook` |
| **Secret** | Generate a strong random string (32+ chars) |
| **Active Events** | âś… `payment.captured` |
| **Alert Email** | Your admin email |

4. Copy the **Webhook Secret** â€” this goes in your `.env` as `RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Your backend verifies every webhook using HMAC SHA256 with `crypto.timingSafeEqual` (see [razorpayService.js:49-61](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/services/razorpayService.js#L49-L61)). This prevents attackers from faking payment confirmations.

### Step 5: Add Keys to Your Server `.env`

Edit your `server/.env` file on the VPS:

```env
# Razorpay â€” LIVE keys for production
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxxxxxxx
RAZORPAY_SECRET=your_live_key_secret_here
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here
```

> [!TIP]
> **Test Mode Shortcut:** Your code has a built-in test mode! If `RAZORPAY_KEY_ID` is set to `rzp_test_xxxxxxxxxxxx` (the placeholder), the backend auto-processes payments without calling Razorpay at all. This is great for development â€” see [paymentController.js:91-137](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/controllers/paymentController.js#L91-L137).

### Step 6: Frontend â€” Razorpay Checkout Script

Already done! Your [index.html](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/index.html#L39) loads the Razorpay checkout script:
```html
<script src="https://checkout.razorpay.com/v1/checkout.js"></script>
```

And your [Register.tsx](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/src/pages/Register.tsx#L205-L233) opens the checkout popup after receiving the order ID from your backend.

### Security Architecture (Already in Place)

| Layer | What Your Code Does | File |
|-------|-------------------|------|
| **Server-side pricing** | Price is NEVER sent from frontend â€” backend looks it up from DB | [paymentController.js:52](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/controllers/paymentController.js#L52) |
| **HMAC webhook verification** | `timingSafeEqual` prevents timing attacks | [razorpayService.js:49](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/services/razorpayService.js#L49) |
| **Atomic status update** | `findOneAndUpdate` with `status: "pending"` filter = idempotent | [paymentController.js:217](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/controllers/paymentController.js#L217) |
| **Always return 200** | Webhook always returns 200 to prevent Razorpay retries | [paymentController.js:251](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/controllers/paymentController.js#L251) |
| **Rate limiting** | Payment: 20 req/15min, Webhook: 50 req/1min | [rateLimiter.js:27-42](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/middleware/rateLimiter.js#L27-L42) |
| **Raw body capture** | Webhook HMAC needs raw body, not parsed JSON | [server.js:82-84](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/server.js#L82-L84) |
| **Duplicate guard** | Rejects if same email+ticketType already paid or pending <30min | [paymentController.js:58-89](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/controllers/paymentController.js#L58-L89) |

