## 2. CI/CD GitHub Secrets Setup

Your CI/CD pipeline uses GitHub Secrets to securely store credentials. **Secrets are encrypted, never visible in logs, and only available to GitHub Actions runners.**

### Required GitHub Secrets

Go to your GitHub repo â†’ **Settings** â†’ **Secrets and variables** â†’ **Actions** â†’ **New repository secret**

#### Backend VPS Deployment Secrets

| Secret Name | What It Is | How to Get It |
|------------|-----------|---------------|
| `VPS_HOST` | Your VPS IP address or domain | e.g. `143.198.xxx.xxx` |
| `VPS_USERNAME` | SSH user on VPS | Usually `root` or a deploy user (see security note below) |
| `VPS_SSH_KEY` | Private SSH key for passwordless login | Generate with `ssh-keygen` (instructions below) |
| `VPS_DEPLOY_PATH` | Absolute path to your app on VPS | e.g. `/home/deploy/cis` or `/var/www/cis` |
| `PRODUCTION_ENV_FILE` | **Entire contents** of your production `.env` | Copy-paste your full `.env` file (all secrets included) |

#### Cloudflare Frontend Secrets

| Secret Name | What It Is | How to Get It |
|------------|-----------|---------------|
| `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` | API token with Pages edit permission | Cloudflare Dashboard â†’ My Profile â†’ API Tokens |
| `CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID` | Your Cloudflare account ID | Visible in dashboard URL or sidebar |

#### Cloudflare Variable (NOT a secret)

Go to **Settings** â†’ **Secrets and variables** â†’ **Actions** â†’ **Variables** tab:

| Variable Name | Value |
|--------------|-------|
| `CLOUDFLARE_PROJECT_NAME` | Name of your Cloudflare Pages project |

### How to Generate SSH Key for VPS

Run this on your local machine:

```bash
# Generate a dedicated deploy key (no passphrase for CI/CD)
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "github-actions-deploy" -f ~/.ssh/cis_deploy_key -N ""

# View the PRIVATE key â€” paste this into GitHub Secret VPS_SSH_KEY
cat ~/.ssh/cis_deploy_key

# View the PUBLIC key â€” add this to VPS
cat ~/.ssh/cis_deploy_key.pub
```

Then on your VPS:

```bash
# Add the public key to authorized_keys
echo "YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE" >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

> [!WARNING]
> **Security Best Practice:** Create a dedicated `deploy` user on your VPS instead of using `root`:
> ```bash
> # On VPS as root
> adduser deploy
> usermod -aG sudo deploy
> mkdir -p /home/deploy/.ssh
> # Add the public key to /home/deploy/.ssh/authorized_keys
> chown -R deploy:deploy /home/deploy/.ssh
> chmod 700 /home/deploy/.ssh
> chmod 600 /home/deploy/.ssh/authorized_keys
> ```
> Then set `VPS_USERNAME` to `deploy`.

### What Goes in `PRODUCTION_ENV_FILE`

This is the **full contents** of your production `.env` file. Paste this as a single GitHub Secret:

```env
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production

# MongoDB
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/cis-prod

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your-super-long-random-string-min-16-chars
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=another-super-long-random-string-min-16-chars

# Razorpay (LIVE keys)
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxxxxxxx
RAZORPAY_SECRET=your_live_secret
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret

# Google Sheets
GOOGLE_CLIENT_EMAIL=your-sa@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=your-sheet-id

# Brevo Email
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-xxxxxxxxxxxx
BREVO_SENDER_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
BREVO_SENDER_NAME=Coastal Innovation Summit

# Admin
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@yourdomain.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=your-strong-admin-password

# Frontend URL (for CORS)
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com
```

> [!CAUTION]
> The `.env` file is written to the server with **chmod 600** (owner-only access) during deploy. See [deploy.yml line 60](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/.github/workflows/deploy.yml#L60). Never `cat` or `echo` it in logs.

