## 3. Cloudflare Pages Setup

### Step 1: Create Cloudflare Account

1. Go to [https://dash.cloudflare.com/sign-up](https://dash.cloudflare.com/sign-up)
2. Create a free account

### Step 2: Create Cloudflare Pages Project

1. Dashboard â†’ **Workers & Pages** â†’ **Create** â†’ **Pages**
2. **Connect to Git** â†’ Authorize GitHub â†’ Select your repo
3. Configure:

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Project name | `cis2026` (or whatever you want) |
| Production branch | `main` |
| Build command | `npm run build` |
| Build output directory | `dist` |
| Root directory | `/` (leave default) |

4. Click **Save and Deploy** (the initial deploy will be manual)

### Step 3: Get API Token

1. Go to **My Profile** (top-right) â†’ **API Tokens**
2. Click **Create Token**
3. Use **Custom Token**:

| Permission | Access |
|-----------|--------|
| Account â†’ Cloudflare Pages | Edit |
| Account â†’ Account Settings | Read |

4. Click **Create Token** â†’ Copy the token

### Step 4: Get Account ID

Your Account ID is visible in:
- The dashboard URL: `https://dash.cloudflare.com/ACCOUNT_ID_HERE/...`
- Or sidebar â†’ scroll to bottom â†’ **Account ID**

### Step 5: Custom Domain (Optional)

1. In your Pages project â†’ **Custom Domains** â†’ **Set up a custom domain**
2. Enter your domain (e.g., `cis2026.com`)
3. Cloudflare will configure DNS automatically if your domain is on Cloudflare

