## 4. VPS Backend Setup

### First-Time Server Setup

```bash
# SSH into your VPS
ssh deploy@YOUR_VPS_IP

# Install Node.js 20
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs

# Install PM2 globally
sudo npm install -g pm2

# Install Nginx
sudo apt install -y nginx

# Create app directory
mkdir -p ~/cis/server

# Copy Nginx config
sudo cp ~/cis/server/deploy/nginx.conf /etc/nginx/sites-available/cis-backend
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/cis-backend /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

# Set up SSL (Let's Encrypt)
sudo apt install -y certbot python3-certbot-nginx
sudo certbot --nginx -d yourdomain.com

# Set up PM2 to start on boot
pm2 startup
# Run the command it tells you to run
```

### After First Deploy (CI/CD handles this automatically)

The [deploy.yml](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/.github/workflows/deploy.yml) workflow will:
1. rsync server files to VPS
2. Write `.env` securely (chmod 600)
3. Sync Nginx config (with `nginx -t` validation)
4. `npm ci --omit=dev`
5. PM2 reload (zero-downtime)
6. Health check `/api/health`

