## 5. Security Checklist

### Before Going Live âś…

- [ ] **Razorpay Live Keys** â€” Replace test keys with live keys in `PRODUCTION_ENV_FILE`
- [ ] **Razorpay Webhook** â€” Create webhook in Razorpay dashboard pointing to `https://yourdomain.com/api/payment/webhook`
- [ ] **Strong JWT Secrets** â€” Generate with: `node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"`
- [ ] **Strong Admin Password** â€” At least 12 characters with uppercase, lowercase, numbers, symbols
- [ ] **MongoDB Atlas IP Whitelist** â€” Add your VPS IP to MongoDB Atlas â†’ Network Access
- [ ] **Nginx domain** â€” Change `yourdomain.com` in [nginx.conf](file:///c:/Users/AYAAN/OneDrive/Desktop/Coastal%20innovation%20summit/server/deploy/nginx.conf) to your actual domain
- [ ] **SSL Certificate** â€” Run `certbot` on VPS
- [ ] **FRONTEND_URL** â€” Set to your actual Cloudflare Pages URL (e.g., `https://cis2026.com`)
- [ ] **CORS will block** â€” If FRONTEND_URL doesn't match the actual frontend domain, API calls will fail
- [ ] **GitHub Secrets** â€” All 7 secrets + 1 variable added (see table above)
- [ ] **Test the flow** â€” Register â†’ Pay â†’ Check email â†’ Check Google Sheets â†’ Check admin dashboard

### Generate Strong Secrets

Run these commands to generate secure random strings:

```bash
# JWT Secret (64 bytes = 128 hex chars)
node -e "console.log('JWT_SECRET=' + require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"

# JWT Refresh Secret
node -e "console.log('JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=' + require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"

# Razorpay Webhook Secret (32 bytes)
node -e "console.log('RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=' + require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```
